'''Whirligig Theatre''' is a [[Theatre of the United Kingdom|British theatre]] company based in [[London]]. It presents full-length musicals and plays in London and on tour.<ref name="Conway1988">{{cite book|last=Conway|first=Robert|title=British Alternative Theatre Directory|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=BjFaAAAAMAAJ|accessdate=27 March 2013|year=1988|publisher=J. Offord|page=118}}</ref> Whirligig was founded in 1979 by [[David Wood (actor)|David Wood]] and John Gould.<ref name="WoodGrant1999">{{cite book|last1=Wood|first1=David|last2=Grant|first2=Janet|title=Theatre for Children: A Guide to Writing, Adapting, Directing, and Acting|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=C1iyjyi9XooC&pg=PT22|accessdate=27 March 2013|date=15 March 1999|publisher=Ivan R. Dee|isbn=978-1-4616-6449-9|pages=22–}}</ref><ref name=playsforyoungaudiences.org>{{cite web|title=Playwright David Wood|url=http://www.playsforyoungaudiences.org/playwrights/david-wood|publisher=Plays for Young Audiences}}</ref> Its first production was the musical, ''The Plotters of Cabbage Patch Corner'' at [[Sadler's Wells Theatre]], London.
